9
00:00:35,170 --> 00:00:37,969
(Today's Webtoon)

10
00:00:56,429 --> 00:00:57,859
Can I have that?

11
00:01:01,130 --> 00:01:02,929
What are you doing here?

12
00:01:08,239 --> 00:01:09,340
That.

13
00:01:10,540 --> 00:01:11,739
Can I have it?

14
00:01:20,489 --> 00:01:25,590
(Episode 10, Stars Don't Disappear. You'll See Them Again One Day)

15
00:01:26,489 --> 00:01:28,628
They say the conditions for the next chief editor...

16
00:01:28,629 --> 00:01:30,230
of Youngtoon are amazing.

17
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:33,400
They're contacting Ji Hyeong.

18
00:01:41,310 --> 00:01:42,409
Are you going home?

19
00:01:45,239 --> 00:01:46,680
Do you want to grab a drink?

20
00:01:48,079 --> 00:01:49,109
Sure.

21
00:01:58,719 --> 00:01:59,819
Ma Eum.

22
00:02:00,489 --> 00:02:01,560
What?

23
00:02:01,790 --> 00:02:03,289
Is he your boyfriend?

24
00:02:03,290 --> 00:02:06,329
No, he's from work.

25
00:02:07,930 --> 00:02:12,139
You were expecting a friend?

26
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:13,300
Bye.

27
00:02:13,639 --> 00:02:16,009
Don't leave. Let's drink together.

28
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:19,280
Right. You're here. You might as well stay.

29
00:02:19,580 --> 00:02:22,550
It's okay. Have a good time.

30
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:25,719
Come on. Stay.

31
00:02:28,189 --> 00:02:31,419
I won't stay for too long.

32
00:02:31,919 --> 00:02:32,960
Sure.

33
00:02:33,090 --> 00:02:35,629
Can we have a glass? Are you having beer?

34
00:02:35,889 --> 00:02:38,399
One beer and Sprite, please.

35
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:39,500
Okay.

36
00:02:41,629 --> 00:02:44,370
- Do you want to sit here? - Relax.

37
00:02:45,740 --> 00:02:49,110
You said it was tough, but no wonder you enjoy working there.

38
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:52,639
Stop it.

39
00:02:55,310 --> 00:02:56,680
It's my mom.

40
00:02:57,120 --> 00:03:00,020
I'm going to answer the call. Don't say anything weird.

41
00:03:00,689 --> 00:03:02,889
Okay. She knows me so well.

42
00:03:06,889 --> 00:03:07,930
Thank you.

43
00:03:11,530 --> 00:03:14,069
Nice to meet you. I'm Ma Eum's friend, Lee Eun Young.

44
00:03:15,099 --> 00:03:17,099
Nice to meet you. I'm Goo Jun Yeong.

45
00:03:17,770 --> 00:03:20,339
We work as a webtoon producer.

46
00:03:20,340 --> 00:03:21,639
How old are you?

47
00:03:22,469 --> 00:03:23,508
I'm 26.

48
00:03:23,509 --> 00:03:25,610
We're friends. Here, let me pour you a glass.

49
00:03:38,389 --> 00:03:40,189
- Thank you. - Stop.

50
00:03:41,430 --> 00:03:44,229
He doesn't drink. You don't drink.

51
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:47,469
Have Sprite.

52
00:03:49,699 --> 00:03:51,699
- Here. - Thank you.

53
00:03:53,069 --> 00:03:54,069
What's going on?

54
00:03:54,639 --> 00:03:57,080
You're the same age, and you work together,

55
00:03:57,379 --> 00:03:58,679
but why are you so polite?

56
00:03:58,680 --> 00:03:59,810
I thought he was older than you.

57
00:04:01,449 --> 00:04:02,449
You think so?

58
00:04:05,250 --> 00:04:07,949
I want it to be casual. Would that make you feel uncomfortable?

59
00:04:08,689 --> 00:04:09,849
No. I like it.

60
00:04:15,030 --> 00:04:18,860
Shall we talk casually too?

61
00:04:22,170 --> 00:04:23,199
Sure.

62
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,300
You said it first.

63
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:28,769
Now, let's get started.

64
00:04:29,069 --> 00:04:30,638
Okay. Let's drink.

65
00:04:30,639 --> 00:04:31,779
What?

66
00:04:33,079 --> 00:04:35,809
How about a toast?

67
00:04:35,810 --> 00:04:37,319
You need to drink too.

68
00:04:38,379 --> 00:04:42,120
Do you want... One... One more glass?

69
00:04:42,790 --> 00:04:43,990
What?

70
00:04:45,220 --> 00:04:47,730
- That was too polite. - Let me pour you a glass.

71
00:04:48,459 --> 00:04:49,490
Good.

72
00:04:49,759 --> 00:04:50,899
Okay.

73
00:04:51,930 --> 00:04:53,000
Between us...

74
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:55,230
You're home.

75
00:04:56,170 --> 00:04:57,239
Where's Ma Eum?

76
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:59,740
She's not home yet. She's having a drink with Eun Young.

77
00:04:59,870 --> 00:05:00,910
Okay.

78
00:05:03,810 --> 00:05:06,938
Honey. Have some watermelon. It's really sweet.

79
00:05:06,939 --> 00:05:08,648
Dad. Have some watermelon. It's so sweet.

80
00:05:08,649 --> 00:05:10,109
- Move. - Why?

81
00:05:10,110 --> 00:05:11,519
Let me go wash my hands.

82
00:05:12,350 --> 00:05:13,790
Why are you telling me to move?

83
00:05:14,889 --> 00:05:18,060
(Ma Eum's Room)

84
00:05:18,290 --> 00:05:21,759
Did Mr. Ma Hae Kyu go to the nursing home?

85
00:05:21,990 --> 00:05:24,329
Yes, he said he'll get rehab.

86
00:05:24,459 --> 00:05:26,899
He asked me to look after Yu Na while he's gone.

87
00:05:27,470 --> 00:05:29,170
- I see. - It's great.

88
00:05:34,670 --> 00:05:36,439
So, what do you want to say?

89
00:05:39,939 --> 00:05:41,209
Say what?

90
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:49,889
I had an offer for Youngtoon chief editor position.

91
00:05:49,990 --> 00:05:54,029
Really? Hey. That's great.

92
00:05:54,129 --> 00:05:57,360
You should've been one already. It's so late.

93
00:05:58,029 --> 00:05:59,259
Congratulations.

94
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:02,970
You're finally on a roll.

95
00:06:07,939 --> 00:06:08,970
I'm happy for you.

96
00:06:09,470 --> 00:06:11,509
It was just an offer.

97
00:06:12,910 --> 00:06:14,980
I didn't want you to hear it from someone else.

98
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:17,349
So I'm telling you now.

99
00:06:17,350 --> 00:06:20,518
You could tell me after accepting the offer.

100
00:06:20,519 --> 00:06:23,688
That's a rare chance. In fact, it's Youngtoon.

101
00:06:23,689 --> 00:06:25,990
Besides, not anyone can be the chief editor.

102
00:06:26,189 --> 00:06:29,328
You need perfect timing...

103
00:06:29,329 --> 00:06:30,698
for the perfect opportunity.

104
00:06:30,699 --> 00:06:33,100
That's really great.

105
00:06:34,300 --> 00:06:35,629
Congratulations.

106
00:06:39,199 --> 00:06:41,139
But this isn't time for that.

107
00:06:48,550 --> 00:06:49,980
You should only think about yourself.

108
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,519
It's here.

109
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,230
Man Chul.

110
00:07:03,829 --> 00:07:04,959
Ji Hyeong.

111
00:07:05,660 --> 00:07:06,829
If I...

112
00:07:07,730 --> 00:07:11,040
change my mind and beg you to stay,

113
00:07:11,100 --> 00:07:13,100
you must...

114
00:07:14,740 --> 00:07:16,470
only think about yourself to the end.

115
00:07:17,740 --> 00:07:20,879
Put yourself in the highest priority.

116
00:07:21,050 --> 00:07:25,180
That's the only advice I can give you...

117
00:07:26,250 --> 00:07:27,790
as your old friend and colleague.

118
00:07:34,189 --> 00:07:35,290
Bye.

119
00:07:41,829 --> 00:07:43,000
Bye.

120
00:07:50,439 --> 00:07:53,910
You should've confirmed the schedule.

121
00:07:54,050 --> 00:07:56,479
He doesn't understand why he should post his cartoon on the internet.

122
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:57,948
He didn't even let me talk about the meeting.

123
00:07:57,949 --> 00:07:59,420
What was I supposed to do?

124
00:08:00,279 --> 00:08:02,588
We were known each other for such a long time.

125
00:08:02,589 --> 00:08:04,489
How could he slam the door in my face?

126
00:08:04,490 --> 00:08:07,328
Did you confirm the meeting schedule with Artist Yeom for tomorrow?

127
00:08:07,329 --> 00:08:08,329
What?

128
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:12,029
Yes.

129
00:08:13,459 --> 00:08:15,730
This job is a total scam.

130
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:20,398
I was moving to another publisher...

131
00:08:20,399 --> 00:08:24,040
It's not a scam. The era of webtoon is coming.

132
00:08:24,939 --> 00:08:25,980
It's going to be huge.

133
00:08:28,379 --> 00:08:31,719
- Huge. - That swindler.

134
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:33,249
(1. Jaemimaru)

135
00:08:33,250 --> 00:08:34,749
(2. Funnytoony)

136
00:08:34,750 --> 00:08:36,619
(4. Webottle or Toonbottle)

137
00:08:36,620 --> 00:08:38,919
(5. Gingertoon?)

138
00:08:40,019 --> 00:08:43,230
Ji Hyeong. What do you think for the logo?

139
00:08:43,659 --> 00:08:44,798
(5. Gingertoon?)

140
00:08:44,799 --> 00:08:46,029
You said you want to name it Gingertoon.

141
00:08:46,159 --> 00:08:47,200
Man Chul.

142
00:08:48,700 --> 00:08:51,398
You can't name a company Shudder...

143
00:08:51,399 --> 00:08:52,939
or use that for the logo.

144
00:08:52,940 --> 00:08:55,638
So I said I'll go with Gingertoon.

145
00:08:55,639 --> 00:08:58,340
Gingerbread cookie is all you can think of for Gingertoon.

146
00:09:04,279 --> 00:09:06,820
Take a photo and copy.

147
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:11,159
The law firm and other...

148
00:09:11,559 --> 00:09:14,860
You should use the second method.

149
00:09:15,259 --> 00:09:17,559
Make it look three dimensional.

150
00:09:17,860 --> 00:09:20,360
For the second step...

151
00:09:23,529 --> 00:09:25,340
Help me.

152
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:28,639
Watch out.

153
00:09:29,509 --> 00:09:32,008
- We have to go now. We're late. - Wait.

154
00:09:32,009 --> 00:09:34,679
- What? - I can't find the contract.

155
00:09:34,710 --> 00:09:36,278
Didn't you leave it there last time?

156
00:09:36,279 --> 00:09:37,849
It's gone.

157
00:09:37,850 --> 00:09:39,120
Here.

158
00:09:40,789 --> 00:09:43,048
Oh, yes. Thank you.

159
00:09:43,049 --> 00:09:44,719
- Where was it? - Here.

160
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:46,359
- Bye. - See you later.

161
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:48,490
Let's go. Bye.

162
00:09:48,559 --> 00:09:49,960
- Thanks, Ae Ri. - Bye.

163
00:09:54,070 --> 00:09:55,100
Everyone.

164
00:09:55,700 --> 00:09:59,740
Mr. Hae Soo is finally joining us!

165
00:10:03,110 --> 00:10:04,179
Wonderful.

166
00:10:09,210 --> 00:10:11,450
This is real.

167
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:13,449
Great.

168
00:10:13,450 --> 00:10:15,989
As soon as he saw the contract, he signed it.

169
00:10:15,990 --> 00:10:17,689
I knew it.

170
00:10:17,690 --> 00:10:20,019
We should take a photo on a day like this.

171
00:10:20,059 --> 00:10:21,829
All right. Ten seconds.

172
00:10:21,830 --> 00:10:24,028
- Hurry up. - Ten seconds.

173
00:10:24,029 --> 00:10:25,199
Go down.

174
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:27,029
Ten seconds are so long.

175
00:10:27,929 --> 00:10:29,099
Keep the contract up.

176
00:10:29,100 --> 00:10:30,469
- Keep smiling. - Keep smiling.

177
00:10:30,470 --> 00:10:31,470
Here we go.

178
00:10:51,460 --> 00:10:53,460
- Assistant Editor Seok? - Yes?

179
00:10:56,960 --> 00:10:59,158
It's the soundtrack production plan.

180
00:10:59,159 --> 00:11:01,299
- Can you go over it? - Okay.

181
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:06,000
Did you...

182
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:08,469
get approval from artists?

183
00:11:08,470 --> 00:11:10,668
Yes. I'm going to tell...

184
00:11:10,669 --> 00:11:12,878
Pomme and Sin Dae Lyug in person today.

185
00:11:12,879 --> 00:11:16,079
Okay. Good luck.

186
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:17,080
Thank you.

187
00:11:18,179 --> 00:11:21,090
By the way, what is all this?

188
00:11:23,950 --> 00:11:25,459
Stuff from Gingertoon.

189
00:11:25,460 --> 00:11:27,220
I see.

190
00:11:33,759 --> 00:11:35,029
Hello.

191
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,369
You're here too.

192
00:11:37,370 --> 00:11:39,399
Because I missed you.

193
00:11:40,070 --> 00:11:41,340
This way.

194
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:46,908
They're my assistants. They're Neon Webtoon producers.

195
00:11:46,909 --> 00:11:47,949
Say hello.

196
00:11:47,950 --> 00:11:49,179
- Hello. - Hello.

197
00:11:50,710 --> 00:11:52,179
Nice to meet you.

198
00:11:52,850 --> 00:11:54,350
I'm Producer On Ma Eum.

199
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:57,120
Hello. I'm Producer Goo Jun Yeong.

200
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:09,970
I'm glad the assistants live nearby.

201
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:12,699
Thanks to you, the work will be done on time.

202
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:13,940
Right?

203
00:12:15,210 --> 00:12:18,210
All you care about is work.

204
00:12:21,809 --> 00:12:23,209
Like I said before,

205
00:12:23,210 --> 00:12:26,049
you're my highest priority.

206
00:12:27,990 --> 00:12:31,220
Well, you don't sound sincere.

207
00:12:31,590 --> 00:12:32,889
Tell her.

208
00:12:34,159 --> 00:12:35,329
About what?

209
00:12:35,330 --> 00:12:38,230
About my sincerity.

210
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:41,129
I'm not sure about it.

211
00:12:42,799 --> 00:12:43,970
Just this once.

212
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:45,899
Well...

213
00:12:47,370 --> 00:12:48,470
I don't know.

214
00:12:50,470 --> 00:12:51,740
I'll do my best.

215
00:13:32,580 --> 00:13:33,620
Mr. Sin.

216
00:13:34,250 --> 00:13:36,289
I told you last time.

217
00:13:36,549 --> 00:13:38,058
The cartoon is important,

218
00:13:38,059 --> 00:13:39,889
but it's not as important as people.

219
00:13:40,789 --> 00:13:44,299
And that includes you too.

220
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:47,929
Eat well,

221
00:13:48,129 --> 00:13:50,500
and sleep well.

222
00:14:06,779 --> 00:14:07,950
I like it.

223
00:14:08,889 --> 00:14:11,820
She's different from the previous characters.

224
00:14:12,590 --> 00:14:15,059
- What do you think? - I like the expression.

225
00:14:16,259 --> 00:14:17,289
But...

226
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:22,200
it looks familiar.

227
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:25,500
You think so?

228
00:14:25,899 --> 00:14:28,539
Nothing looks similar to me.

229
00:14:31,379 --> 00:14:35,009
If you're okay with it, I'll color it and finish it up.

230
00:14:35,779 --> 00:14:36,779
Okay.

231
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:39,250
Have you checked the document on the soundtrack?

232
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:43,750
I think Ji Hyeong will move to Youngtoon.

233
00:14:44,519 --> 00:14:47,090
- What? - You scared me.

234
00:14:47,629 --> 00:14:50,629
Why would Assistant Editor Seok go to Youngtoon?

235
00:14:50,889 --> 00:14:52,799
He gets a lot of offers.

236
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:55,668
But he already refused Youngtoon once.

237
00:14:55,669 --> 00:14:57,398
When we closed Gingertoon, he didn't go to Youngtoon...

238
00:14:57,399 --> 00:14:58,839
and came here with us.

239
00:14:58,840 --> 00:15:00,539
It's different this time.

240
00:15:01,009 --> 00:15:02,509
It's the chief editor position.

241
00:15:04,639 --> 00:15:06,710
The chief editor position...

242
00:15:07,779 --> 00:15:10,009
is a rare chance.

243
00:15:10,250 --> 00:15:11,980
Yes, that'd come with conditions...

244
00:15:12,549 --> 00:15:15,620
that he can't possibly refuse.

245
00:15:21,490 --> 00:15:22,659
Youngtoon?

246
00:15:40,509 --> 00:15:42,110
Where are you going? Do you have a meeting?

247
00:15:42,710 --> 00:15:44,279
To meet Oh Yoon.

248
00:15:45,519 --> 00:15:47,480
- Did you make up your mind? - Yes.

249
00:15:49,889 --> 00:15:51,590
It still won't be easy.

250
00:15:54,759 --> 00:15:56,259
Bye.

251
00:15:59,259 --> 00:16:01,269
Do you want me to get you cheongsimhwan?

252
00:16:04,570 --> 00:16:05,639
Good luck.

253
00:16:27,490 --> 00:16:28,889
Darn it.

254
00:16:34,629 --> 00:16:35,700
Nice.

255
00:16:35,830 --> 00:16:38,600
Only two more to go.

256
00:16:42,340 --> 00:16:45,340
What the heck? I'm winning.

257
00:16:53,179 --> 00:16:55,719
I texted you many times that I'll visit you today,

258
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:56,990
but you didn't respond.

259
00:16:57,960 --> 00:17:00,720
I called you in front of your house, but you didn't answer it.

260
00:17:03,159 --> 00:17:04,759
I didn't know. I was too busy.

261
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:14,670
It's tough, isn't it?

262
00:17:15,539 --> 00:17:17,069
You can barely make a progress.

263
00:17:23,710 --> 00:17:25,519
It's always been tough.

264
00:17:26,579 --> 00:17:28,890
This isn't my first time drawing.

265
00:17:29,319 --> 00:17:31,190
Sometimes I'm stuck.

266
00:17:32,789 --> 00:17:34,190
I'm sure it'll all work out.

267
00:17:39,299 --> 00:17:40,529
You think so?

268
00:17:42,329 --> 00:17:45,140
You've never been in the bottom rank for this long before.

269
00:17:46,670 --> 00:17:48,710
You'd been exhausted,

270
00:17:49,210 --> 00:17:51,108
but you were never lost.

271
00:17:51,109 --> 00:17:52,410
I'm not lost.

272
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:55,509
I'm doing my own thing,

273
00:17:55,609 --> 00:17:58,920
but people don't see it. That's frustrating.

274
00:18:00,049 --> 00:18:02,250
It suddenly got me thinking...

275
00:18:04,019 --> 00:18:05,819
if I made a wrong choice.

276
00:18:10,059 --> 00:18:12,230
Did I make a wrong choice?

277
00:18:17,430 --> 00:18:18,599
What the heck?

278
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:22,069
You liked it when I described it.

279
00:18:22,269 --> 00:18:23,568
You said it was good.

280
00:18:23,569 --> 00:18:24,980
You said you wanted to publish it.

281
00:18:29,849 --> 00:18:30,950
I'm sorry.

282
00:18:32,349 --> 00:18:34,450
- It's my fault. - What?

283
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:40,519
If I can go back in time...

284
00:18:40,690 --> 00:18:42,390
If I get a chance again,

285
00:18:44,359 --> 00:18:47,230
I would've plucked up my courage and went against it.

286
00:18:47,630 --> 00:18:49,799
I wanted to follow your opinion.

287
00:18:49,970 --> 00:18:51,569
I was afraid...

288
00:18:52,039 --> 00:18:54,670
you might move somewhere else if I go against your idea.

289
00:18:56,069 --> 00:18:57,910
I neglected my duty.

290
00:18:58,779 --> 00:19:01,349
When I first read "The Beginning of Men" synopsis and rough draft,

291
00:19:01,950 --> 00:19:03,680
it was hard to understand and abstruse.

292
00:19:04,880 --> 00:19:08,190
I also thought you won't be able to prove your real worth in that genre.

293
00:19:10,119 --> 00:19:11,660
What's my real worth?

294
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:16,289
Being silly?

295
00:19:17,759 --> 00:19:19,960
You make everyone happy.

296
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:26,140
So, it's a cartoon for comedy?

297
00:19:26,670 --> 00:19:29,009
I don't feel like laughing.

298
00:19:30,269 --> 00:19:33,440
(Darn parents.)

299
00:19:36,410 --> 00:19:38,579
Don't give in.

300
00:19:39,420 --> 00:19:41,920
I thought I met a genius.

301
00:19:46,759 --> 00:19:47,759
What?

302
00:19:49,059 --> 00:19:51,460
- What is it? - It's so...

303
00:19:51,700 --> 00:19:53,259
Look at you.

304
00:19:53,759 --> 00:19:56,329
- I'm okay. - What's wrong with you?

305
00:19:57,900 --> 00:19:59,200
Geez.

306
00:19:59,740 --> 00:20:01,538
Do you remember the first thing I said...

307
00:20:01,539 --> 00:20:03,509
- when I met you? - This is crazy.

308
00:20:11,319 --> 00:20:13,680
"The world needs your cartoon."

309
00:20:14,819 --> 00:20:17,619
Anyone who reads your cartoon...

310
00:20:20,190 --> 00:20:22,029
will be truly happy at least for that moment.

311
00:20:25,259 --> 00:20:28,230
Right. That's what you said.

312
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:35,440
I was really excited to hear that.

313
00:20:40,509 --> 00:20:41,778
I thought I won't be able to debut...

314
00:20:41,779 --> 00:20:44,210
after Gingertoon closed.

315
00:20:45,349 --> 00:20:47,750
But I had a flashy debut in Neon thanks to you.

316
00:20:59,700 --> 00:21:01,400
You put your faith in me back then.

317
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:07,069
Please trust my opinion just once more.

318
00:21:08,609 --> 00:21:12,210
Your sense of humor is warm, not cynical or biting.

319
00:21:13,140 --> 00:21:14,480
It's humane.

320
00:21:16,609 --> 00:21:18,778
And I know you started "The Beginning of Men"...

321
00:21:18,779 --> 00:21:20,220
to show that humanism.

322
00:21:20,920 --> 00:21:22,849
This isn't just about the sales numbers.

323
00:21:23,390 --> 00:21:25,960
Even for your sake, it's better to decide quickly.

324
00:21:27,619 --> 00:21:29,960
I've arrived at this decision after long, careful consideration.

325
00:21:31,529 --> 00:21:34,599
If you think I'm wrong, you can go ahead and scold me.

326
00:21:35,069 --> 00:21:36,569
But as your producer, I, Choi Du Hee,

327
00:21:39,400 --> 00:21:41,539
believe that you should end "The Beginning of Men" here...

328
00:21:43,809 --> 00:21:46,980
and aim for a successful comeback with a new project.

329
00:22:09,670 --> 00:22:11,329
People who said my work lacked depth...

330
00:22:13,269 --> 00:22:16,470
and that I'd amassed popularity only due to my looks and the TV shows...

331
00:22:18,539 --> 00:22:20,839
I really wanted to prove them wrong.

332
00:22:21,480 --> 00:22:23,910
And those who said I could only make funny webtoons.

333
00:22:24,650 --> 00:22:26,680
I wanted to silence them for good.

334
00:22:42,329 --> 00:22:43,470
Mr. Oh.

335
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:47,740
You see, making someone laugh...

336
00:22:49,369 --> 00:22:50,839
It's the hardest thing to do.

337
00:22:55,410 --> 00:22:58,420
And in this country, no one can beat you on that front.

338
00:23:01,380 --> 00:23:04,450
I hope you can take pride in that.

339
00:23:09,230 --> 00:23:10,490
Producer Choi...

340
00:23:34,750 --> 00:23:36,750
(You can do it!)

341
00:23:37,619 --> 00:23:39,990
I never once imagined the office...

342
00:23:40,119 --> 00:23:42,160
without Assistant Editor Seok.

343
00:23:57,670 --> 00:23:58,940
It's five dollars.

344
00:24:00,809 --> 00:24:03,049
- I'll get the same one. - Sure.

345
00:24:03,609 --> 00:24:04,650
Wait, but...

346
00:24:06,920 --> 00:24:07,920
Thanks.

347
00:24:11,450 --> 00:24:14,720
Ever since I heard Mr. Seok might leave Neon,

348
00:24:16,130 --> 00:24:17,759
I've been having a hard time focusing on work.

349
00:24:17,890 --> 00:24:19,700
Just because of that?

350
00:24:20,829 --> 00:24:24,000
- What? - I mean, people change jobs often.

351
00:24:24,569 --> 00:24:27,639
Besides, if they're offering him the chief editor position,

352
00:24:27,640 --> 00:24:28,739
we should congratulate him.

353
00:24:28,740 --> 00:24:30,740
Yes, you're absolutely right.

354
00:24:31,009 --> 00:24:33,339
We should totally congratulate him.

355
00:24:34,809 --> 00:24:37,549
It's just that I'm a little sad.

356
00:24:40,720 --> 00:24:42,190
He's my first mentor, you know.

357
00:24:45,220 --> 00:24:47,259
I guess you emotionally relied on him a lot.

358
00:24:48,589 --> 00:24:49,589
Yes.

359
00:24:51,160 --> 00:24:52,299
I certainly did.

360
00:24:55,529 --> 00:24:57,029
And I learned so much from him.

361
00:24:58,799 --> 00:25:00,369
But all I did was cause trouble...

362
00:25:01,069 --> 00:25:03,039
and make him clean up my mess.

363
00:25:04,670 --> 00:25:06,539
I would've tried to learn things more quickly...

364
00:25:09,049 --> 00:25:10,809
had I known he'd leave the company so soon.

365
00:25:21,359 --> 00:25:22,430
Are you feeling hot?

366
00:25:25,299 --> 00:25:26,400
No, I'm good.

367
00:25:31,329 --> 00:25:33,269
(Answer Right Away)

368
00:25:34,539 --> 00:25:35,609
I'll be right back.

369
00:25:43,079 --> 00:25:44,109
Yes.

370
00:25:56,430 --> 00:25:57,890
Do you work out too?

371
00:25:58,630 --> 00:26:01,329
These days, nothing's more important than taking care of yourself.

372
00:26:01,869 --> 00:26:04,829
I go for a run from time to time to clear my head.

373
00:26:04,970 --> 00:26:08,099
Come on. You need more than just cardio exercises.

374
00:26:08,509 --> 00:26:12,910
A real man must lift weights.

375
00:26:13,910 --> 00:26:14,910
Right.

376
00:26:20,220 --> 00:26:21,950
- Sorry? - The towel.

377
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:27,190
Thank you.

378
00:26:35,799 --> 00:26:38,470
Is there something else you need me to do?

379
00:26:39,140 --> 00:26:41,099
I believe I've sent you all the reports you needed.

380
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:43,039
- Are you sure? - Yes.

381
00:26:43,210 --> 00:26:45,880
You think you've covered everything I needed?

382
00:26:50,480 --> 00:26:52,078
Based on the reports you sent last time,

383
00:26:52,079 --> 00:26:54,649
it seems like Mr. Kwon's projects take up a large portion...

384
00:26:54,650 --> 00:26:55,719
of the team's sales.

385
00:26:55,720 --> 00:26:59,359
I'd like to view his list of artists and other files.

386
00:26:59,660 --> 00:27:02,930
Oh, those are his personal files.

387
00:27:06,730 --> 00:27:09,369
Right, and I want to see them.

388
00:27:10,630 --> 00:27:14,499
It's risky for the team to let just one producer...

389
00:27:14,500 --> 00:27:16,069
dominate everyone else in sales.

390
00:27:16,440 --> 00:27:18,809
And he's the only one who has access to all the key info and data?

391
00:27:19,339 --> 00:27:22,380
I think it's dangerous to let him thrive all alone.

392
00:27:23,180 --> 00:27:25,220
Nothing bad will come out of me having access to the info.

393
00:27:29,819 --> 00:27:31,859
What's this? Raise your arm.

394
00:27:35,160 --> 00:27:36,829
You said you only did cardio.

395
00:27:59,420 --> 00:28:01,420
It's a talisman. My good luck talisman.

396
00:28:03,490 --> 00:28:06,390
You gave me this on the day of my interview.

397
00:28:07,160 --> 00:28:08,220
Right!

398
00:28:09,559 --> 00:28:11,389
But you didn't pass the interview that day.

399
00:28:11,390 --> 00:28:14,130
Regardless, I got the job and am sitting here now.

400
00:28:21,640 --> 00:28:23,140
Mr. Seok!

401
00:28:24,410 --> 00:28:25,740
You scared me.

402
00:28:27,740 --> 00:28:29,079
What are you doing here?

403
00:28:33,950 --> 00:28:35,519
(Little Tent Bar)

404
00:28:44,130 --> 00:28:46,259
Hey, what's the matter?

405
00:28:48,869 --> 00:28:50,170
Did something happen?

406
00:28:54,569 --> 00:28:56,710
- Yes. - What? What happened?

407
00:29:01,910 --> 00:29:04,680
I heard you were getting bumped up.

408
00:29:05,319 --> 00:29:08,079
Hey, where did you learn that expression?

409
00:29:08,250 --> 00:29:09,789
Back when I was doing judo,

410
00:29:10,019 --> 00:29:12,159
my seniors said that when our coaches or head coaches...

411
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:14,789
were moving forward in their careers.

412
00:29:16,329 --> 00:29:17,329
I see.

413
00:29:19,329 --> 00:29:22,369
Anyway, who told you that I was getting bumped up?

414
00:29:24,269 --> 00:29:27,240
Mr. Kwon told me.

415
00:29:27,799 --> 00:29:29,969
He said you were probably going to join Youngtoon...

416
00:29:29,970 --> 00:29:32,140
as their new chief editor.

417
00:29:32,539 --> 00:29:34,440
He said rumors were running rampant.

418
00:29:34,609 --> 00:29:37,180
- Mr. Kwon said that? - Yes.

419
00:29:39,549 --> 00:29:42,089
But that's not true.

420
00:29:44,390 --> 00:29:47,089
- Sorry? - I haven't decided yet.

421
00:29:47,990 --> 00:29:50,059
They did approach me with the offer, but...

422
00:29:50,789 --> 00:29:51,829
Oh.

423
00:29:54,430 --> 00:29:58,670
Does it mean you might turn down the offer?

424
00:29:59,039 --> 00:30:00,069
Yes.

425
00:30:01,099 --> 00:30:04,140
Why? Do you want me to stay?

426
00:30:04,440 --> 00:30:07,278
I know it's not my place to say this...

427
00:30:07,279 --> 00:30:09,379
and that I'm being selfish.

428
00:30:09,380 --> 00:30:11,849
But of course, I want you to stay.

429
00:30:12,920 --> 00:30:16,588
But everyone says that you won't be able to turn it down...

430
00:30:16,589 --> 00:30:20,390
as it's an amazing opportunity, so I don't know what to say.

431
00:30:29,329 --> 00:30:30,970
Right, it is a great opportunity.

432
00:30:33,700 --> 00:30:35,910
There are many people who want that position.

433
00:30:38,579 --> 00:30:40,809
Then how come you haven't made up your mind yet?

434
00:30:43,079 --> 00:30:46,250
Well... Just because everyone wants it,

435
00:30:47,279 --> 00:30:49,890
it doesn't mean I have to want it too.

436
00:30:51,119 --> 00:30:52,490
So I'm really trying...

437
00:30:53,890 --> 00:30:55,890
to listen to my heart.

438
00:30:57,829 --> 00:30:59,500
To figure out what I really want...

439
00:31:00,259 --> 00:31:01,700
and what I should choose...

440
00:31:02,130 --> 00:31:03,670
to make sure I won't regret my decision later on.

441
00:31:13,079 --> 00:31:14,309
Oh, it's okay.

442
00:31:22,420 --> 00:31:23,819
- One moment. - Okay.

443
00:31:25,589 --> 00:31:26,690
Yes, what's up?

444
00:31:30,490 --> 00:31:31,690
Okay, all right.

445
00:31:32,599 --> 00:31:34,059
No, I'll meet you there.

446
00:31:35,299 --> 00:31:36,299
Okay.

447
00:31:41,299 --> 00:31:42,440
Well...

448
00:31:43,769 --> 00:31:45,710
You should go home. I'll see you tomorrow at work.

449
00:31:45,910 --> 00:31:48,380
- Okay. - All right, bye.

450
00:31:50,849 --> 00:31:52,180
Wait, Mr. Seok!

451
00:31:55,420 --> 00:31:56,420
Yes?

452
00:31:59,289 --> 00:32:00,319
It's nothing.

453
00:32:01,160 --> 00:32:02,259
Get home safely.

454
00:32:17,569 --> 00:32:20,380
(Fifty cents)

455
00:32:42,099 --> 00:32:43,329
(Fifty cents)

456
00:32:46,369 --> 00:32:47,700
(Fifty cents)

457
00:33:03,450 --> 00:33:04,618
(Search Mail)

458
00:33:04,619 --> 00:33:05,720
(Homework)

459
00:33:07,819 --> 00:33:10,359
(To: Seok Ji Hyeong)

460
00:33:13,759 --> 00:33:16,500
What does it mean to be an editor?

461
00:33:17,599 --> 00:33:18,769
In short.

462
00:33:22,470 --> 00:33:24,609
It is your job to find the answer.

463
00:33:25,069 --> 00:33:27,480
Oh, me? I see, okay.

464
00:33:28,440 --> 00:33:31,949
Starting next month, you are to send me the answers you find.

465
00:33:31,950 --> 00:33:33,019
One a month. Got it?

466
00:33:37,619 --> 00:33:39,690
(Read, Unread)

467
00:33:50,930 --> 00:33:52,740
(Inbox, Compose)

468
00:33:54,200 --> 00:33:55,809
(September homework)

469
00:33:58,710 --> 00:34:01,640
(An editor is...)

470
00:34:09,519 --> 00:34:11,219
Why are you still undecided?

471
00:34:11,920 --> 00:34:13,760
It's an amazing offer.

472
00:34:14,889 --> 00:34:16,760
Everyone is different and considers different things...

473
00:34:17,360 --> 00:34:18,900
when making a career decision.

474
00:34:21,260 --> 00:34:23,000
I keep thinking...

475
00:34:24,230 --> 00:34:26,738
that you're a better fit for the position.

476
00:34:26,739 --> 00:34:28,300
Why did they approach me?

477
00:34:29,139 --> 00:34:30,670
Because I want to be with you.

478
00:34:37,710 --> 00:34:39,719
I need to learn more from you.

479
00:34:39,980 --> 00:34:42,820
Just like you chose Neon...

480
00:34:43,119 --> 00:34:44,820
because of Mr. Jang Man Chul,

481
00:34:45,320 --> 00:34:48,519
I chose you as my chief editor.

482
00:34:51,289 --> 00:34:53,000
The choice you made back then...

483
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:56,530
Have you ever regretted it?

484
00:34:58,969 --> 00:35:00,199
This may be...

485
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:03,539
your last chance...

486
00:35:04,909 --> 00:35:06,110
to fix it.

487
00:35:06,380 --> 00:35:07,510
(Our deepest condolences)

488
00:35:09,449 --> 00:35:11,250
(Our most heartfelt condolences)

489
00:35:20,960 --> 00:35:22,090
(Goo Ae Ri, Sophia)

490
00:35:25,630 --> 00:35:27,630
(Our deepest condolences)

491
00:35:37,570 --> 00:35:38,670
Please calm down.

492
00:35:46,280 --> 00:35:48,650
(Our deepest condolences)

493
00:36:00,900 --> 00:36:03,300
Why won't you accept the offer?

494
00:36:03,530 --> 00:36:06,000
Shouldn't you be grateful that you got an offer from Youngtoon?

495
00:36:06,070 --> 00:36:07,300
In the midst of all this!

496
00:36:07,670 --> 00:36:08,739
Ji Hyeong.

497
00:36:09,639 --> 00:36:11,510
Let's be realistic here.

498
00:36:13,440 --> 00:36:15,510
I don't care about people bad-mouthing me.

499
00:36:16,650 --> 00:36:17,880
I just...

500
00:36:18,880 --> 00:36:20,449
need you.

501
00:36:25,050 --> 00:36:26,059
Ji Hyeong.

502
00:36:28,590 --> 00:36:29,960
I guess it was all an excuse.

503
00:36:31,130 --> 00:36:32,400
An excuse? What do you mean?

504
00:36:34,400 --> 00:36:35,630
You...

505
00:36:37,500 --> 00:36:39,869
You chose Mr. Jang,

506
00:36:43,809 --> 00:36:44,969
not me.

507
00:36:47,739 --> 00:36:48,980
(Seoul)

508
00:37:13,670 --> 00:37:14,670
("Do Re Mi Fa Sol La Ti Do")

509
00:37:21,710 --> 00:37:25,849
(September homework, Unread)

510
00:37:52,909 --> 00:37:54,880
- Mr. Seok. - Yes.

511
00:37:55,880 --> 00:37:57,780
I sent you an email yesterday. Did you see it?

512
00:37:58,679 --> 00:38:01,118
Remember the homework? Summarizing what it means to be an editor.

513
00:38:01,119 --> 00:38:03,948
I sent it to you yesterday.

514
00:38:03,949 --> 00:38:07,420
Oh, that. Whether I check or not isn't important.

515
00:38:07,590 --> 00:38:09,829
What matters is that you do it every month.

516
00:38:10,960 --> 00:38:12,030
Right.

517
00:38:15,530 --> 00:38:16,868
You'd better not slack off...

518
00:38:16,869 --> 00:38:19,439
or skip the homework altogether just because I'm not checking.

519
00:38:19,440 --> 00:38:20,539
Of course, I won't.

520
00:38:20,940 --> 00:38:23,969
That homework is always my number one priority.

521
00:38:24,670 --> 00:38:25,780
You're doing a great job.

522
00:38:33,320 --> 00:38:34,380
Sorry, one moment.

523
00:38:35,889 --> 00:38:38,389
Hello, Mr. Na. How have you been?

524
00:38:38,550 --> 00:38:40,920
Mr. Seok, are you moving to Youngtoon?

525
00:38:44,030 --> 00:38:45,090
So the rumors are true.

526
00:38:45,699 --> 00:38:48,658
You practically begged me not to go to Youngtoon.

527
00:38:48,659 --> 00:38:51,829
And you're joining Youngtoon as their new chief editor?

528
00:38:53,170 --> 00:38:56,039
I feel so betrayed.

529
00:38:56,239 --> 00:38:59,379
Listen. Nothing's been decided yet.

530
00:38:59,380 --> 00:39:01,610
Well, I was mad at you when I first heard the rumors.

531
00:39:02,750 --> 00:39:04,380
But then, I thought about it,

532
00:39:05,280 --> 00:39:07,920
and it is about time you got the chief editor title.

533
00:39:08,420 --> 00:39:10,218
Besides, if you're Youngtoon's chief editor,

534
00:39:10,219 --> 00:39:13,219
it'll be easier for me to move to Youngtoon later on.

535
00:39:13,820 --> 00:39:16,889
I don't think it's a bad idea.

536
00:39:18,289 --> 00:39:19,760
Do you want to go to Youngtoon?

537
00:39:20,329 --> 00:39:21,360
No.

538
00:39:24,570 --> 00:39:26,500
But you never know.

539
00:39:27,099 --> 00:39:29,210
This industry is changing rapidly these days.

540
00:39:33,010 --> 00:39:35,779
And let's be honest. If you have the chief editor title,

541
00:39:35,780 --> 00:39:38,949
it's a good thing for me, no matter which company you work for.

542
00:39:39,250 --> 00:39:40,280
Am I wrong?

543
00:39:45,150 --> 00:39:47,288
Okay, call me when you're done.

544
00:39:47,289 --> 00:39:48,320
Yes.

545
00:39:49,690 --> 00:39:50,730
Sure.

