549
00:40:08,380 --> 00:40:09,780
What are you looking at?

550
00:40:11,579 --> 00:40:13,150
Your daughter is so cute.

551
00:40:14,219 --> 00:40:15,280
He's a boy.

552
00:40:17,889 --> 00:40:19,019
Just kidding.

553
00:40:19,519 --> 00:40:20,889
Isn't Ji Woo adorable?

554
00:40:21,719 --> 00:40:24,289
I want her to join a girl group when she's older.

555
00:40:29,429 --> 00:40:31,699
What? Are you curious about these files?

556
00:40:34,699 --> 00:40:36,468
I'll show you when you're more experienced.

557
00:40:36,469 --> 00:40:38,969
You won't understand a thing even if I show you now. Just do your work.

558
00:40:39,739 --> 00:40:40,809
Okay.

559
00:40:47,420 --> 00:40:48,650
(Kwon Young Bae, 2022-2023 Tentative Lists of Artists)

560
00:40:50,519 --> 00:40:51,519
(2022-2023 Tentative Lists of Artists)

561
00:40:54,260 --> 00:40:56,860
(From Kwon Young Bae, To Goo Jun Yeong)

562
00:40:58,230 --> 00:41:00,130
I need to use the restroom.

563
00:41:00,960 --> 00:41:01,960
Mr. Kwon.

564
00:41:01,961 --> 00:41:04,428
You won't understand a thing, but feel free to go through them.

565
00:41:04,429 --> 00:41:07,469
Go through them and let me know if you have any suggestions.

566
00:41:08,199 --> 00:41:10,010
This is why all the rookies love me.

567
00:41:19,780 --> 00:41:20,849
Watch.

568
00:41:30,389 --> 00:41:31,460
Now, look.

569
00:41:32,190 --> 00:41:33,559
You can do stuff like this too.

570
00:41:35,929 --> 00:41:37,969
- Isn't it so cool? - Wow, yes.

571
00:41:38,170 --> 00:41:41,940
I've been really enjoying learning about these effects and using them.

572
00:41:42,369 --> 00:41:44,268
Since there are different layers,

573
00:41:44,269 --> 00:41:47,480
you can create and check different versions. It's really fun.

574
00:41:47,840 --> 00:41:51,750
There's still so much to learn even at this old age.

575
00:41:52,309 --> 00:41:55,050
It's not easy, but I'm grateful.

576
00:41:56,489 --> 00:41:58,289
You really inspire me.

577
00:42:00,289 --> 00:42:03,659
Anyway, are you worried about something?

578
00:42:04,460 --> 00:42:05,530
Oh.

579
00:42:06,500 --> 00:42:08,000
Do I look worried?

580
00:42:10,469 --> 00:42:11,630
Yes.

581
00:42:13,039 --> 00:42:14,599
I don't know what the problem is,

582
00:42:16,070 --> 00:42:20,010
but try to carefully separate your thoughts into layers.

583
00:42:21,409 --> 00:42:24,480
Turn off the overlapping layers one by one...

584
00:42:25,280 --> 00:42:27,550
and observe each layer carefully.

585
00:42:27,949 --> 00:42:31,050
It'll help you get to the essence of the problem.

586
00:42:39,760 --> 00:42:40,760
Okay.

587
00:43:10,559 --> 00:43:11,929
You're here alone today?

588
00:43:14,159 --> 00:43:16,170
The chief editor was here alone yesterday too.

589
00:43:16,400 --> 00:43:18,499
Oh, I see.

590
00:43:18,500 --> 00:43:20,739
- Enjoy. - Thank you.

591
00:43:30,610 --> 00:43:32,110
(1 unread message, Youngtoon CEO)

592
00:43:32,949 --> 00:43:34,780
Mr. Seok.

593
00:43:34,980 --> 00:43:37,389
You can let me know of your decision by the end of the week, right?

594
00:43:42,929 --> 00:43:44,889
I sent you an email yesterday. Did you see it?

595
00:43:53,699 --> 00:43:57,210
(On Ma Eum, May homework)

596
00:43:58,909 --> 00:44:02,179
An editor is the webtoon artists' biggest cheerleader.

597
00:44:02,340 --> 00:44:05,909
Your drawing style... I mean, there's nothing wrong...

598
00:44:06,380 --> 00:44:07,849
with your drawings.

599
00:44:07,920 --> 00:44:10,749
That's right. So if the problem was that...

600
00:44:10,750 --> 00:44:12,960
you kept hunching your back while working on your drawings,

601
00:44:13,059 --> 00:44:14,718
I suggest you tweak the angle...

602
00:44:14,719 --> 00:44:17,129
of your drawing board, so it's not tilted.

603
00:44:17,130 --> 00:44:20,659
Then I can create drawings that I won't be embarrassed of?

604
00:44:21,000 --> 00:44:22,500
Yes, that's correct.

605
00:44:22,969 --> 00:44:26,339
You must always help your artists believe that they can do it...

606
00:44:26,340 --> 00:44:28,070
and boost their confidence.

607
00:44:29,469 --> 00:44:32,409
An editor is the artists' solutionist.

608
00:44:34,010 --> 00:44:35,340
No, we can't do that.

609
00:44:35,409 --> 00:44:36,750
Where are you right now?

610
00:44:37,079 --> 00:44:39,448
I'm on my way to find his girlfriend.

611
00:44:39,449 --> 00:44:40,880
- What? - Promise me.

612
00:44:41,849 --> 00:44:43,448
- Promise. - Good stuff.

613
00:44:43,449 --> 00:44:45,288
You must do whatever it takes to make sure...

614
00:44:45,289 --> 00:44:46,690
your artists meet their deadlines.

615
00:44:49,389 --> 00:44:52,530
An editor is the artists' running mate.

616
00:44:54,829 --> 00:44:57,829
- One, two. - One, two. That's it.

617
00:44:58,000 --> 00:45:00,670
The artists are all running their own long marathons.

618
00:45:00,900 --> 00:45:03,069
You must be willing to become their other leg...

619
00:45:03,070 --> 00:45:04,739
- One, two! - and complete the race with them.

620
00:45:07,239 --> 00:45:08,579
"Weapon Feeb"?

621
00:45:09,010 --> 00:45:10,578
Wait, you are...

622
00:45:10,579 --> 00:45:12,210
Sin Dae Lyug?

623
00:45:14,849 --> 00:45:16,949
An editor is like Christopher Columbus.

624
00:45:17,650 --> 00:45:20,360
To discover talented new artists,

625
00:45:20,690 --> 00:45:22,989
you don't hesitate to embark on a long, adventurous journey.

626
00:45:25,389 --> 00:45:26,500
This is good.

627
00:45:28,659 --> 00:45:31,500
An editor is like a gardener.

628
00:45:32,300 --> 00:45:34,940
- Eat well. - Eat well...

629
00:45:35,300 --> 00:45:37,710
- And? - and sleep well.

630
00:45:39,210 --> 00:45:40,880
You put your faith in me back then.

631
00:45:41,440 --> 00:45:43,250
Please trust my opinion just once more.

632
00:45:45,010 --> 00:45:46,150
We're rooting for you, Yu Na!

633
00:45:48,320 --> 00:45:49,519
I'm really sorry.

634
00:45:50,449 --> 00:45:53,519
A gardener who tends to and looks after...

635
00:45:53,860 --> 00:45:57,159
countless trees and flowers called webtoon artists.

636
00:45:58,059 --> 00:46:00,860
At times, you get pricked by a rose thorn,

637
00:46:01,059 --> 00:46:02,659
which leaves a scar.

638
00:46:03,530 --> 00:46:07,940
And there are times when you have no choice but to trim...

639
00:46:08,269 --> 00:46:09,439
some overgrown branches.

640
00:46:09,440 --> 00:46:12,539
On Ma Eum. Think carefully.

641
00:46:13,010 --> 00:46:16,849
Without the readers, we don't have a place here.

642
00:46:17,809 --> 00:46:20,250
This department and everyone here.

643
00:46:20,719 --> 00:46:23,750
It is the gardener's job to take good care...

644
00:46:23,820 --> 00:46:25,889
of all the trees and plants...

645
00:46:26,690 --> 00:46:29,159
so they'd produce flowers and fruits in the best possible condition.

646
00:46:31,159 --> 00:46:33,730
Then many people will visit the garden...

647
00:46:34,429 --> 00:46:37,170
and admire their beauty to the fullest.

648
00:46:37,730 --> 00:46:40,339
(Webtoon, Web Novels)

649
00:46:40,340 --> 00:46:42,199
(Recently Read)

650
00:46:45,210 --> 00:46:47,109
("More Than Girls," "Princess Kumiho")

651
00:46:47,110 --> 00:46:48,839
("Weapon Feeb," "Full Count")

652
00:46:48,840 --> 00:46:50,449
("The Dream of the Dragon")

653
00:46:50,949 --> 00:46:52,750
She's right.

654
00:47:05,460 --> 00:47:06,530
Ma Eum.

655
00:47:07,300 --> 00:47:08,329
Mr. Seok.

656
00:47:08,900 --> 00:47:09,969
You're still here.

657
00:47:10,099 --> 00:47:11,469
Yes.

658
00:47:13,400 --> 00:47:14,400
Oh, right.

659
00:47:15,500 --> 00:47:17,070
You diligently did your homework.

660
00:47:17,969 --> 00:47:19,110
You read it?

661
00:47:20,510 --> 00:47:22,879
Great job. You put me to shame.

662
00:47:22,880 --> 00:47:24,449
Gosh, no way.

663
00:47:25,409 --> 00:47:26,480
I mean it.

664
00:47:28,880 --> 00:47:29,989
Many years ago,

665
00:47:31,250 --> 00:47:34,289
when Mr. Jang told me to do that as homework,

666
00:47:34,360 --> 00:47:38,659
I only wrote like two sentences.

667
00:47:57,980 --> 00:48:00,550
I don't want to bother you when you're working. I'm off.

668
00:48:01,119 --> 00:48:02,579
No, it's fine.

669
00:48:03,389 --> 00:48:04,820
I'm off. I'll see you tomorrow.

670
00:48:15,699 --> 00:48:17,170
I will see you tomorrow.

