(July 2022, Sales list per producer)

674
00:48:37,219 --> 00:48:39,719
(Title, Payout Per Episode)

675
00:48:51,800 --> 00:48:53,969
- Hello? - It's me.

676
00:48:56,000 --> 00:48:57,139
Who is this?

677
00:49:06,849 --> 00:49:08,750
I said we should meet another time, Uncle.

678
00:49:10,349 --> 00:49:12,949
Why? So you can change your number and go AWOL on me again?

679
00:49:16,429 --> 00:49:18,960
Goodness. Why are you treating me like a loan shark?

680
00:49:19,090 --> 00:49:20,360
What do you want from me?

681
00:49:22,800 --> 00:49:23,968
Help us out with our living expenses.

682
00:49:23,969 --> 00:49:26,029
We only lived at your place for a few months.

683
00:49:26,030 --> 00:49:29,300
We were always walking on eggshells and ate the bare minimum to survive.

684
00:49:30,510 --> 00:49:32,239
- Have some shame, will you? - Hey.

685
00:49:32,869 --> 00:49:34,479
You can't do this to me.

686
00:49:34,480 --> 00:49:36,908
You were abroad when Ae Ri died.

687
00:49:36,909 --> 00:49:38,449
Who held a funeral for her?

688
00:49:39,050 --> 00:49:42,919
I was the most heartbroken when your sister died.

689
00:49:42,920 --> 00:49:46,150
I was the only one who sincerely cried.

690
00:49:46,320 --> 00:49:48,760
That's why I'm here, to see you for one last time.

691
00:49:50,389 --> 00:49:53,800
Enjoy the food. And do not visit me at work again.

692
00:49:54,699 --> 00:49:56,800
You brat. You're such an ingrate.

693
00:49:58,030 --> 00:50:01,500
I did my best to raise you two for my late sister's sake.

694
00:50:07,039 --> 00:50:08,940
You took my parents' insurance payout.

695
00:50:09,480 --> 00:50:10,650
On top of that,

696
00:50:11,449 --> 00:50:13,980
you took the money Ae Ri earned from her part-time jobs.

697
00:50:14,949 --> 00:50:16,280
You were heartbroken when she died?

698
00:50:17,289 --> 00:50:19,420
I bet you were just angry because your meal ticket was gone.

699
00:50:24,929 --> 00:50:26,899
(Spicy Beef Soup, Bulgogi)

700
00:50:26,900 --> 00:50:29,559
Hey, Producer Goo. Did you have lunch?

701
00:50:30,369 --> 00:50:33,639
Spicy beef soup... Never mind.

702
00:50:34,139 --> 00:50:35,400
I'll see you in the office.

703
00:50:40,610 --> 00:50:41,840
Jun Yeong! Wait.

704
00:50:43,809 --> 00:50:45,150
How do you know that man?

705
00:50:46,079 --> 00:50:48,949
It was him. It was his fault that Ae Ri died.

706
00:51:33,059 --> 00:51:34,730
What brings you all the way here?

707
00:51:35,760 --> 00:51:36,900
I've made my decision.

708
00:51:39,400 --> 00:51:41,500
I figured I should let you know sooner than later.

709
00:52:04,590 --> 00:52:07,130
What? What is it? Is there a problem?

710
00:52:13,699 --> 00:52:16,070
No. Everything's fine.

711
00:52:36,320 --> 00:52:37,329
Jun Yeong.

712
00:52:38,329 --> 00:52:39,389
We're all going out...

713
00:52:40,030 --> 00:52:41,629
for an impromptu team dinner today.

714
00:52:41,630 --> 00:52:43,670
At a beef barbecue restaurant. Awesome, right?

715
00:52:44,199 --> 00:52:46,469
- Yes. - You don't like beef?

716
00:52:47,699 --> 00:52:49,639
- I do. - Right? It's awesome.

717
00:52:51,670 --> 00:52:53,509
"Awesome"? Are you serious?

718
00:52:53,510 --> 00:52:55,510
This is our farewell dinner for Mr. Seok.

719
00:52:55,809 --> 00:52:59,409
Goodness. Read the room, will you?

720
00:53:00,650 --> 00:53:01,820
Oh, dear.

721
00:53:10,230 --> 00:53:12,059
I'm going to pig out today.

722
00:53:16,699 --> 00:53:18,530
What's with you today? You're scaring me.

723
00:53:18,630 --> 00:53:20,739
What? What's the problem?

724
00:53:21,570 --> 00:53:23,869
You never join us when we have a team dinner.

725
00:53:24,469 --> 00:53:26,309
We're having beef today, Hanwoo.

726
00:53:27,739 --> 00:53:31,479
He's here because this is Mr. Seok's farewell dinner.

727
00:53:31,480 --> 00:53:32,808
Farewell dinner? Come on.

728
00:53:32,809 --> 00:53:35,178
If you take a taxi there, you won't pay more than the base fare.

729
00:53:35,179 --> 00:53:36,479
Don't make such a fuss.

730
00:53:36,480 --> 00:53:38,819
We know how you feel. You're acting all tough,

731
00:53:38,820 --> 00:53:42,159
but you'd hate to see him leave. No one's sadder than you are.

732
00:53:42,989 --> 00:53:44,030
Mr. Kwon.

733
00:53:44,590 --> 00:53:45,989
You must be on pins and needles...

734
00:53:46,260 --> 00:53:48,229
because you don't want to be promoted to assistant editor.

735
00:53:48,230 --> 00:53:50,869
I already told you guys loud and clear. I won't do it.

736
00:53:51,130 --> 00:53:53,768
Why not? You'll be great at it.

737
00:53:53,769 --> 00:53:54,839
Why would I? I'm not crazy.

738
00:53:54,840 --> 00:53:56,569
I'd have to work a lot, and it's stressful.

739
00:53:56,570 --> 00:53:58,169
I'll get nothing but empty compliments.

740
00:53:58,170 --> 00:53:59,610
You're clueless.

741
00:53:59,909 --> 00:54:01,440
But you'll get a raise.

742
00:54:01,940 --> 00:54:03,649
You really are clueless.

743
00:54:03,650 --> 00:54:05,609
It'll be a tiny pay raise.

744
00:54:05,610 --> 00:54:08,320
It's peanuts compared to the commission he currently earns.

745
00:54:09,019 --> 00:54:10,050
Yes, you know how it works.

746
00:54:12,090 --> 00:54:15,690
There is probably zero chance that Mr. Seok will decide to stay, right?

747
00:54:16,090 --> 00:54:17,429
How would I know?

748
00:54:18,230 --> 00:54:21,429
He should accept the offer. I mean, for his own sake.

749
00:54:27,500 --> 00:54:29,670
Hey, what are you doing? Pouring your own drink?

750
00:54:30,039 --> 00:54:31,170
Jun Yeong.

751
00:54:32,010 --> 00:54:33,110
Here, let me.

752
00:54:33,809 --> 00:54:35,679
Oh, you guys have dropped the honorifics.

753
00:54:37,309 --> 00:54:38,309
Yes.

754
00:54:42,179 --> 00:54:43,349
Hey, Ma Eum.

755
00:54:43,590 --> 00:54:45,219
You're already downing your drinks?

756
00:54:46,889 --> 00:54:49,760
She must be sad. Mr. Seok was her first mentor.

757
00:54:50,460 --> 00:54:53,289
Goodness. Take it down a notch, will you?

758
00:54:55,300 --> 00:54:57,468
A team dinner? Why, all of a sudden?

759
00:54:57,469 --> 00:54:58,630
And Hanwoo at that?

760
00:54:59,030 --> 00:55:01,170
I want to treat you to a nice dinner before you leave.

761
00:55:01,670 --> 00:55:03,710
Hey, I have something to tell you.

762
00:55:03,909 --> 00:55:06,138
We can talk when we sit down. Everyone is waiting for us.

763
00:55:06,139 --> 00:55:08,440
- Come on. - Wait, but...

764
00:55:08,610 --> 00:55:09,939
I'm full. I ate too much.

765
00:55:09,940 --> 00:55:10,948
- You made it. - There they are.

766
00:55:10,949 --> 00:55:12,949
- You're here. - You don't need to get up.

767
00:55:13,920 --> 00:55:16,920
- The man of the hour is here. - Why am I the man of the hour?

768
00:55:17,449 --> 00:55:19,789
Come on. We already know.

769
00:55:20,690 --> 00:55:21,819
Know what?

770
00:55:21,820 --> 00:55:23,630
That you're leaving Neon.

771
00:55:32,030 --> 00:55:34,900
It looks like I was the only one who didn't know.

772
00:55:35,500 --> 00:55:36,969
Yes, that's why we're here.

773
00:55:37,409 --> 00:55:41,679
All right. As you all know...

774
00:55:47,380 --> 00:55:49,119
Mr. Seok and I...

775
00:55:52,550 --> 00:55:54,988
have been working together...

776
00:55:54,989 --> 00:55:57,658
since our Gingertoon days, but Youngtoon...

777
00:55:57,659 --> 00:55:59,730
Stop! Wait.

778
00:56:01,559 --> 00:56:02,860
Do you want to tell them yourself?

779
00:56:03,599 --> 00:56:04,929
Yes, let me tell them.

780
00:56:10,739 --> 00:56:11,940
(Wooam Hanwoo)

781
00:56:15,409 --> 00:56:17,210
- Well, I... - Wait.

782
00:56:19,949 --> 00:56:21,849
- What are you doing? - Let go.

783
00:56:24,590 --> 00:56:26,190
What's with you today? You're scaring me...

784
00:56:33,429 --> 00:56:34,829
Say something cool.

785
00:56:43,170 --> 00:56:47,380
I know what you're all thinking now.

786
00:56:47,980 --> 00:56:51,250
And I know about the rumors that have been going around.

787
00:56:52,010 --> 00:56:54,949
- But... - Sorry, one moment.

788
00:56:55,449 --> 00:56:57,819
I really wasn't going to cry.

789
00:56:57,820 --> 00:56:59,449
My gosh.

790
00:57:00,590 --> 00:57:03,059
- What's with her? - Mr. Seok.

791
00:57:05,789 --> 00:57:09,299
I'll do better! Can you please stay?

792
00:57:09,300 --> 00:57:10,469
My gosh...

793
00:57:12,429 --> 00:57:15,369
Oh, boy. She's drunk.

794
00:57:17,570 --> 00:57:18,670
I'm not going anywhere.

795
00:57:18,809 --> 00:57:20,940
Yes, don't leave us.

796
00:57:22,210 --> 00:57:24,280
Yes, I'm not leaving.

797
00:57:27,349 --> 00:57:28,380
What?

798
00:57:32,420 --> 00:57:33,590
Don't worry.

799
00:57:34,559 --> 00:57:36,389
- Really? - Yes.

800
00:57:37,730 --> 00:57:39,489
- I decided to stay. - What?

801
00:57:40,300 --> 00:57:41,630
What? Seriously?

802
00:57:42,300 --> 00:57:43,429
But why?

803
00:57:46,699 --> 00:57:49,300
Have you lost your mind? Are you serious?

804
00:57:50,869 --> 00:57:52,570
Yes, I'm serious.

805
00:57:54,480 --> 00:57:56,849
I've been thinking hard...

806
00:57:58,510 --> 00:58:02,150
to figure out why I'm so hesitant to leave Neon.

807
00:58:03,320 --> 00:58:05,820
Is it because I feel indebted, like you said?

808
00:58:07,690 --> 00:58:11,489
Or is it because I'm afraid to take on a new challenge?

809
00:58:14,199 --> 00:58:15,329
I kept trying...

810
00:58:17,170 --> 00:58:18,769
to listen to my heart.

811
00:58:21,039 --> 00:58:22,239
But you see,

812
00:58:24,039 --> 00:58:27,639
I want to stay so I can take responsibility...

813
00:58:28,440 --> 00:58:30,280
for the new projects I've started...

814
00:58:32,780 --> 00:58:34,480
and the people I've met.

815
00:58:36,579 --> 00:58:40,320
I planted all these trees and flower seeds...

816
00:58:41,690 --> 00:58:44,559
in the garden called Neon. I want to see them grow well...

817
00:58:46,789 --> 00:58:48,329
and produce good fruits.

818
00:58:49,829 --> 00:58:51,099
I'm sorry to tell you this,

819
00:58:52,269 --> 00:58:56,440
but they might get rid of your desk next year.

820
00:58:57,610 --> 00:58:58,869
What do you mean?

821
00:58:59,070 --> 00:59:02,980
Neon's higher-ups are planning to acquire Youngtoon.

822
00:59:06,349 --> 00:59:09,920
I decided to stay because there is still a lot of work to be done.

823
00:59:12,190 --> 00:59:13,289
And...

824
00:59:14,420 --> 00:59:16,860
it looks like I also have some babysitting to do.

825
00:59:19,329 --> 00:59:22,860
Anyway, let's stop talking about this.

826
00:59:23,059 --> 00:59:24,499
Ma Eum, stop crying.

827
00:59:24,500 --> 00:59:26,598
Let's enjoy the meat.

828
00:59:26,599 --> 00:59:27,869
- Okay! - Sounds good!

829
00:59:27,969 --> 00:59:29,138
- All right. - Let's drink.

830
00:59:29,139 --> 00:59:30,909
- Oh, my. - How about a toast?

831
00:59:30,969 --> 00:59:34,279
Here's to Mr. Seok Ji Hyeong!

832
00:59:34,280 --> 00:59:35,638
- Cheers! - Cheers!

833
00:59:35,639 --> 00:59:36,979
- Stop overreacting. - Whatever.

834
00:59:36,980 --> 00:59:37,980
Cheers!

835
00:59:37,981 --> 00:59:39,808
Here's to Mr. Seok Ji Hyeong!

836
00:59:39,809 --> 00:59:41,118
- Cheers! - Cheers!

837
00:59:41,119 --> 00:59:42,380
Hey, Ji Hyeong.

838
00:59:42,619 --> 00:59:44,190
Okay, hang on.

839
00:59:45,989 --> 00:59:47,959
Oh, that's too much.

840
00:59:47,960 --> 00:59:51,859
Then how about we toast to the editorial department?

841
00:59:51,860 --> 00:59:53,059
- Sure. - Sounds good.

842
00:59:53,829 --> 00:59:55,658
Here's to the success of the editorial department!

843
00:59:55,659 --> 00:59:58,269
- Cheers! - Cheers!

844
00:59:58,500 --> 01:00:00,769
We're whole again!

845
01:00:01,800 --> 01:00:03,809
- Why did you turn down the offer? - Way to go!

846
01:00:04,369 --> 01:00:05,409
Seriously.

847
01:00:07,710 --> 01:00:09,280
Thank you, Ms. Kim.

848
01:00:09,510 --> 01:00:11,579
I know you kindly gave me such an amazing offer,

849
01:00:11,650 --> 01:00:13,210
but I still have a lot to learn.

850
01:00:14,420 --> 01:00:16,780
I think Ms. Jang Hye Mi is a great fit for the position.

851
01:00:17,619 --> 01:00:18,650
Right.

852
01:00:22,289 --> 01:00:23,489
Thank you.

853
01:00:24,190 --> 01:00:25,190
Take care.

854
01:00:36,000 --> 01:00:37,239
Hey, why are you here?

855
01:00:38,409 --> 01:00:39,610
Mr. Seok.

856
01:00:41,340 --> 01:00:42,909
I want to ask you something.

857
01:00:44,309 --> 01:00:46,079
Sure, what is it?

858
01:00:53,989 --> 01:00:55,260
Do you know this person?

859
01:01:10,940 --> 01:01:13,340
How do you know her?

860
01:02:05,230 --> 01:02:07,929
(Today's Webtoon)

861
01:02:08,300 --> 01:02:11,269
Do you remember that girl Ae Ri we used to work with at Gingertoon?

862
01:02:11,570 --> 01:02:13,369
Do you know if she had family members?

863
01:02:13,630 --> 01:02:15,468
Since you've moved now,

864
01:02:15,469 --> 01:02:18,139
I hope that only new and good things happen to you.

865
01:02:18,940 --> 01:02:20,908
You had her thinking that you'd make her...

866
01:02:20,909 --> 01:02:22,210
into a full-time employee.

867
01:02:23,980 --> 01:02:27,079
Excuse me, don't you recognize me from the webtoon department?

868
01:02:27,750 --> 01:02:29,018
What are you doing here?

869
01:02:29,019 --> 01:02:30,619
I had some documents to give you.

870
01:02:30,849 --> 01:02:33,389
That friend of ours was the reason...

871
01:02:33,590 --> 01:02:35,489
why we make webtoons.

872
01:02:36,119 --> 01:02:39,360
She's Jun Yeong's sister?
